# Third-Party Dependencies and Licenses

## Production Dependencies

### Core (used by all modules)

All core production dependencies are licensed under Apache 2.0 or MIT:

- **Kotlin** (Apache 2.0) — language and stdlib, used by every module
- **kotlinx-coroutines** (Apache 2.0) — used by `:api` and every tool for streaming I/O
- **kotlinx-io** (Apache 2.0) — used by `:api` for `RawSource`/`RawSink` pipe plumbing
- **kotlinx-serialization** (Apache 2.0) — used by `:tools:jq` for JSON parsing/emission
- **Koin** — `koin-core` and `koin-annotations` (Apache 2.0) — DI container used by every tool's `@Module` registration
- **antlr-kotlin-runtime** (`com.strumenta:antlr-kotlin-runtime`, Apache 2.0) — runtime for the ANTLR-generated kash parser in `:core`

### Tool-specific dependencies

Most shipped tools (`basename`, `chmod`, `cut`, `dirname`, `head`, `ls`, `mkdir`,
`rm`, `rmdir`, `seq`, `shasum`, `sleep`, `sort`, `stat`, `tail`, `tee`, `touch`,
`tr`, `uniq`, `wc`, `xargs`) have no third-party runtime dependencies beyond
the core stack above — they are pure Kotlin implementations against
`:api`.

The following tools pull in additional third-party libraries:

- **`:tools:grep`, `:tools:find`, `:tools:sed`, `:tools:jq`** — depend on
  `:shared:regex`, which on JVM uses **re2j** (Google, Apache 2.0). RE2/J
  is used in place of `java.util.regex` to guarantee linear-time matching
  and avoid ReDoS on adversarial patterns.
- **`:tools:jq`** — additionally uses **kotlinx-serialization-json**
  (Apache 2.0) for JSON I/O.
- **`:tools:python3`** — no third-party deps; defines the `PythonEngine`
  SPI only.
- **`:tools:python3-graalpy`** — JVM-only engine implementation backed by
  **GraalPy** (`org.graalvm.polyglot:polyglot`, `:python`, and
  `org.graalvm.python:python-embedding`, all v25.0.2), plus the
  transitively-pulled GraalVM SDK / Truffle / shadowed runtime artifacts
  (`org.graalvm.sdk:*`, `org.graalvm.truffle:*`, `org.graalvm.shadowed:*`).
  All GraalVM Polyglot and GraalPy artifacts are distributed by Oracle
  under the **Universal Permissive License v1.0 (UPL)**. GraalPy bundles
  a Python runtime that includes components under their own licenses
  (CPython / Python Software Foundation License, plus various
  PSF-compatible licenses for stdlib modules). Only modules that depend
  on `:tools:python3-graalpy` (currently `:kash-app` on JVM) ship these
  libraries.
- **`:tools:kash:git-jgit`** — JVM-only host driver that backs the
  kash `git` tool against a real Eclipse JGit repository (in-memory or
  on-disk). Depends on **Eclipse JGit** (`org.eclipse.jgit:org.eclipse.jgit`,
  v7.6.0.202603022253-r). JGit is distributed by the Eclipse Foundation
  under the **Eclipse Distribution License v1.0**, which is a verbatim
  copy of the **3-clause BSD license** — Apache-2.0 compatible. Upstream:
  https://github.com/eclipse-jgit/jgit. Only modules that depend on
  `:tools:kash:git-jgit` ship this library; the core kash `git` tool
  (`:tools:kash:git`) has zero JGit linkage and runs on every target
  including wasmJs.
- **`:tools:kash:git-http`** — common-source (JVM + wasmJs) host driver
  that backs the kash `git` tool against any smart-HTTP-v0 git server
  via `:shared:net`. Pure-Kotlin; no third-party Kotlin libraries beyond
  what `:shared:net` already pulls in. Fetch-only in v1 (clone/fetch
  works; push is rejected with a "no transport configured" message).
- **`pako`** (npm) — JavaScript port of zlib used by `:tools:kash:git` on
  wasmJs for loose-object and packfile deflate/inflate. Retained for git
  specifically because pako exposes `strm.total_in` on its `Inflate`
  class, which the pack-file parser needs to advance its read cursor;
  fflate's maintainer closed the equivalent request as not-planned
  (fflate#221). Dual-licensed **MIT AND Zlib** (both permissive,
  Apache-2.0 compatible). Upstream: https://github.com/nodeca/pako.
  Bundled by webpack into the wasm app artifact; pulled in via
  `npm("pako", …)` from `tools/kash/git/build.gradle.kts`. JVM builds do
  not depend on pako (they use `java.util.zip`).
- **`fflate`** (npm) — pure-JavaScript deflate/inflate + ZIP archive
  library used by `:tools:ext:gzip`, `:tools:ext:tar`, and
  `:tools:ext:zip` on wasmJs. Licensed **MIT** (permissive, Apache-2.0
  compatible). Upstream: https://github.com/101arrowz/fflate. Bundled by
  webpack into the wasm app artifact; pulled in via `npm("fflate", …)`
  from each tool's `build.gradle.kts`. JVM builds use `java.util.zip` /
  Apache Commons Compress instead and do not depend on fflate.
- **coi-serviceworker** (Guido Zuidhof and contributors) — small JavaScript
  service worker vendored verbatim (v0.1.7) at
  `kash-app-web/src/wasmJsMain/resources/coi-serviceworker.js`. It re-injects
  the Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy / Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy headers on
  static hosts that can't set them (GitHub Pages), so the page becomes
  cross-origin isolated and SharedArrayBuffer (the Pyodide-in-Worker stdin
  pipe) is available. Licensed **MIT** (permissive, Apache-2.0 compatible).
  Upstream: https://github.com/gzuidhof/coi-serviceworker. Shipped only in the
  `:kash-app-web` wasmJs distribution; not used by JVM builds.

